a time for justice is a 1994 american short documentary film produced by charles guggenheim .   it won an academy award in 1995 for documentary short subject .   the film was produced by guggenheim and the southern poverty law center .   this 38-minute film , narrated by julian bond and featuring john lewis , presents a short history of the civil rights movement using historical footage and spoken accounts of participants .   events recounted are the montgomery bus boycott ; school integration in little rock , arkansas ; demonstrations in birmingham ; and the 1965 selma to montgomery march for voting rights .